reviews.text: Everything sold here is same as Pizza Hut. Price are a bit lower than Pizza Hut. The main difference are the pizza. it's because they put less ingredients on top. A lot less Cheese. Which makes me think it's better to go to Pizza Hut. Well it's better for those who think price first and the taste second.

No matter how your food taste, service and attitude can make good tasting food garbage...  This is the case with this venue. Pizza and fried chicken isn't bad for Hong Kong.  Unfortunately the workers here must feel they are something special..  Poor and rude attitude!  Really left a bad taste in my mouth on 2 occasions now and won't let there be a 3rd.
Ok...Ok
A low grade version of Pizza Hut at a lower price. Focus on take away but can eat in with few tables, similar to the take away Pizza Hut nearby.

There is a Pizza Hut near by but this place offers the same quality for a cheaper price. Pizza taste just as good as Pizza Hut and less greasy. Went there twice to buy pizza for my son. I would go back again.
